FBIS3-13153 "drnes047_l_94005" FBIS-NES-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Report Criticizes Security at Site of Massacre TA0603061794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 6 Mar 94 TA0603061794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The closure on the West Bank and Gaza is continuing, with Palestinians still banned from leaving for jobs inside Israel. Security sources told Qol Yisra'el it remains extremely difficult to protect the Jewish settlers living in Hebron. Brigadier David Agmon, who investigated the Hebron massacre for the chief of staff, has confirmed that Barukh Goldstein was the only person to fire inside the Cave of the Patriarchs. His report, presented to the chief of staff at the weekend, also criticized security procedures at the site.
